# Design Packet Lifecycle

## When this applies

When the draft-technical-document skill produces a polished document whose source is a design packet (any file under a design_packet/ directory).

## Required steps

After the published document has been written to docs/design/published/:

1. Delete every source file from the originating design_packet/ directory.
2. Remove the design_packet/ directory if it is now empty. Walk from leaves upward if nested.
3. State which files were deleted in the response.

## Rationale

A design packet is a transient handoff artifact. Once its content lives as a polished published document, the packet is redundant and must be removed to avoid stale duplicates.
